# Recharts Data Visualization Guide for Aucctus

Create data visualizations using Recharts that follow Aucctus design patterns.

**📚 Official Recharts Documentation**: https://recharts.github.io/en-US/api/

---

## When to Use This Guide

Use charts when you need to:
- Visualize trends over time
- Compare values across categories
- Show distributions or proportions
- Display relationships between variables
- Present financial projections with uncertainty
- Illustrate market data or competitive analysis

---

## Quick Start

```typescript
import {
  LineChart, Line, XAxis, YAxis, Tooltip,
  ResponsiveContainer
} from 'recharts';

// Always wrap charts in ResponsiveContainer
<ResponsiveContainer width='100%' height='100%'>
  <LineChart data={data}>
    <XAxis dataKey='month' {...aucctusAxisStyle} />
    <YAxis {...aucctusAxisStyle} />
    <Tooltip content={<CustomTooltip />} />
    <Line
      dataKey='value'
      stroke='#7c3aed'
      strokeWidth={2.5}
      dot={false}
    />
  </LineChart>
</ResponsiveContainer>
```

---

## Aucctus Chart Container Pattern

**Every chart should follow this structure:**

```typescript
<div className='aucctus-bg-primary aucctus-border-secondary rounded-lg border p-2'>
  <div className='p-4'>
    {/* Header */}
    <div className='mb-3'>
      <h3 className='aucctus-header-xs-medium aucctus-text-primary'>
        Chart Title
      </h3>
      <p className='aucctus-text-sm aucctus-text-tertiary'>
        Subtitle or context
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* Chart */}
    <div className='h-72 w-full'>
      <ResponsiveContainer width='100%' height='100%'>
        {/* Recharts component */}
      </ResponsiveContainer>
    </div>

    {/* Legend (if needed) */}
    <div className='mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 md:grid-cols-4'>
      {legendItems.map(item => (
        <div className='flex items-center gap-2'>
          <div className='h-3 w-3 rounded-full' style={{ backgroundColor: item.color }} />
          <span className='aucctus-text-xs aucctus-text-secondary'>{item.label}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

